<item>
            <title>[LU-2071] Memory leak in procfs handling</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2071</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There seems to be a minor memory leak in all versions of lustre since at least Feb 2007.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The name##_seq_open does single_open, but corresponding lprocfs_seq_release does seq_release instead of single_release, and as such a bit of memory allocated in single_open remains not freed.&lt;br/&gt;
As such every call to lctl leaks 32 bytes.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
